1
00:00:49,450 --> 00:00:52,317
[ Man ] ALREADY CHECKED         
CORRIDOR 2. NOTHING THERE.      
[ Man #2 ] ANYTHING AT ALL?     


2
00:00:52,386 --> 00:00:54,452
                WHERE IS HE?    
        FIND HIM!               


3
00:00:54,521 --> 00:00:56,454
<i>[ Buzzer Blaring ]</i>              
                <i> COME ON, GO!</i>   
                <i> LET'S GO!</i>      


4
00:01:28,155 --> 00:01:30,489
<i>[ Buzzer Sounding,</i>              
<i>  Helicopter Whirring ]</i>         


5
00:01:34,461 --> 00:01:37,229
<i>[ Ship's Horn Sounding ]</i>        


6
00:01:37,298 --> 00:01:40,832
<i>♪♪ [ Man Vocalizing</i>             
<i>     "Jingle Bells" ]</i>           


7
00:01:44,571 --> 00:01:47,406
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>WELL, I GUESS MAMA WON'T BE</i>     
<i>KISSING SANTA CLAUS THIS YEAR.</i>  


8
00:01:48,876 --> 00:01:50,843
                JUST TELL ME    
                WHAT YOU SAW.   


9
00:01:50,911 --> 00:01:53,912
HEY, I'M JUST AN ELF.           
I DO WHAT I'M TOLD. YOU KNOW?   


10
00:01:53,981 --> 00:01:58,116
"BE JOLLY"? BESIDES,            
I HAVEN'T SEEN THE BIG GUY      
SINCE THE PARTY LAST NIGHT.     


11
00:01:58,185 --> 00:02:01,220
                    OH, YEAH?   
            WHEN ARE YOU GONNA  
            SHOVEL HIM OUT?     


12
00:02:01,288 --> 00:02:03,221
                SOON ENOUGH.    
                THE MEAT WAGON  
                JUST GOT HERE.  


13
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:06,457
DON'T YOU MEAN                  
THE "MEAT SLEIGH"?              
                HO, HO, HO.     


14
00:02:07,861 --> 00:02:09,861
            HEY.                
                    <i> [ Cop ]</i>    
                    <i> EVENIN'.</i>   


15
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:14,199
        <i> OKAY. GOT A LIVE ONE.</i>  


16
00:02:16,236 --> 00:02:18,870
        - A LIVE ONE?           
        - IT'S A JOKE.          


17
00:02:18,939 --> 00:02:21,105
                SNOWBLOWERS MUST
                HAVE BURIED HIM.


18
00:02:21,174 --> 00:02:23,375
        <i> [ Jarod ]</i>              
        <i> IS THAT... SANTA CLAUS?</i>


19
00:02:23,443 --> 00:02:25,377
<i>YEAH. THE RED HAT'S</i>             
<i>A DEAD GIVEAWAY.</i>                


20
00:02:25,446 --> 00:02:27,812
        ANYBODY GOT A SHOVEL?   
NO.                             


21
00:02:29,383 --> 00:02:31,583
BUT I'VE GOT THE GIFT WRAP.     


22
00:02:31,652 --> 00:02:35,154
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


23
00:03:28,842 --> 00:03:31,976
            <i> THANKS, GUS.</i>       


24
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:35,280
<i>DR. DRAKE? THESE JUST CAME</i>      
<i>IN FROM THE MAYOR'S OFFICE.</i>     


25
00:03:35,349 --> 00:03:38,082
    - SAME GIFT AS LAST YEAR?   
    - SMELLS LIKE IT.           


26
00:03:38,151 --> 00:03:40,118
OH, WELL.                       
'TIS THE SEASON, FUGIMORA.      


27
00:03:40,187 --> 00:03:43,521
<i>PASS 'EM OUT.</i>                   
<i>WE'LL SEE WHO</i>                   
<i>SURVIVES THIS YEAR.</i>             


28
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:46,257
        YES, MA'AM.             


29
00:03:46,326 --> 00:03:50,162
- UH, SO, HOW'S                 
  THE NEW GUY DOIN'?            
-<i> A LOT BETTER THAN SANTA.</i>      


30
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:57,936
            DRINKING ON THE JOB?
            ACTUALLY, THIS      
            WAS FROM THE SCENE. 


31
00:03:59,473 --> 00:04:03,808
DR. JAROD MARLEY?               
MEET DR. LISABETH DRAKE,        
OUR CHIEF CORONER.              


32
00:04:03,877 --> 00:04:05,944
HELLO.                          
HI. YOU FINISHED WITH ST. NICK? 


33
00:04:06,013 --> 00:04:08,813
    - YES, I AM.                
    - [ Man Clearing Throat ]   


34
00:04:08,882 --> 00:04:12,150
    DETECTIVE GUERRA.           
    GEE, RIGHT ON TIME.         


35
00:04:12,219 --> 00:04:15,853
-<i> NOW, CAN WE DO THIS?</i>          
- VICTIM IS NOT KRISS KRINGLE,  


36
00:04:15,923 --> 00:04:19,057
        AS WE FIRST SUSPECTED,  
        BUT A THEODORE HARGROVE,


37
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:23,361
58, STOCKBROKER,                
PLAYED SANTA AT ONE HELL OF     
A CHRISTMAS PARTY DOWNTOWN.     


38
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:28,299
        GO AHEAD, DOCTOR.       
HE DIED OF A COMBINATION OF     
FACTORS, MAINLY A HEART ATTACK. 


39
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:30,602
        KIM, I THOUGHT WE WERE  
        GOING WITH EXPOSURE.    


40
00:04:30,671 --> 00:04:34,006
WELL, THAT WAS MY FIRST         
INSTINCT, BUT FURTHER           
EXAMINATION REVEALED THE TRUTH. 


41
00:04:34,074 --> 00:04:38,277
HEART ATTACK MAKES SENSE.       
FOLKS AT THE OFFICE PARTY       
SAID ST. NICK WAS DOIN'...      


42
00:04:38,345 --> 00:04:41,179
- ONE HELL OF                   
  A LAMBADA THAT NIGHT.         
- I DON'T KNOW WHO "LAMBADA" IS,


43
00:04:41,247 --> 00:04:45,016
        BUT, YES, LIVIDITY WAS  
        AFFECTED BY THE COLD.   


44
00:04:45,085 --> 00:04:48,954
<i>BUT THE BLOOD DISTRIBUTION</i>      
<i>IN THE LEG MUSCLES WOULD SUGGEST</i>
<i>HE WAS DOING STRENUOUS ACTS.</i>    


45
00:04:49,022 --> 00:04:51,523
WHAT ABOUT TIME OF DEATH?       
<i>[ Dr. Drake ]</i>                   
<i>NO WAY.</i>                         


46
00:04:51,591 --> 00:04:53,458
        WE CAN'T PULL THAT OFF  
        IN THIS WEATHER.        


47
00:04:53,526 --> 00:04:56,661
            ACTUALLY, THAT'S    
            WHERE THIS CAME IN. 


48
00:04:56,730 --> 00:05:00,799
<i>THE EGGNOG WAS HARD WHEN</i>        
<i>WE FOUND IT, BUT IT WASN'T</i>      
<i>COMPLETELY FROZEN THROUGH.</i>      


49
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:03,534
MAINLY BECAUSE MR. HARGROVE     
HAD QUITE A BIT OF BRANDY IN IT.


50
00:05:03,603 --> 00:05:07,505
- OH, THERE'S A SHOCKER.        
-<i> THE MILK HAD TIME TO CURDLE.</i>  


51
00:05:07,574 --> 00:05:09,907
    SO I COMPARED THE BACTERIA  
    LEVELS IN THE CUP...        


52
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:11,910
        WITH THAT OF THE SAMPLE 
        THAT FELL ON THE SNOW,  


53
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:15,714
AND I DEDUCED THAT MR. HARGROVE 
SUCCUMBED TO HIS HEART ATTACK...


54
00:05:15,783 --> 00:05:19,184
            SOMEWHERE BETWEEN   
            1:45 AND 2:00 A.M.  


55
00:05:19,252 --> 00:05:22,954
            MY GUESS WOULD BE   
            1:48-ISH.           


56
00:05:23,022 --> 00:05:25,857
    - [ Whistles ]              
    - I ASK FOR AN AUTOPSY,     
      HE GIVES ME EGGNOG.       


57
00:05:25,926 --> 00:05:28,059
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>               


58
00:05:28,128 --> 00:05:31,730
            YEP? OKAY.          


59
00:05:33,733 --> 00:05:36,100
DR. DRAKE? THE DELEGATION       
FROM THE MAYOR'S OFFICE IS HERE.


60
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:38,770
            DAMN! THEY'RE EARLY.
            WE'RE DONE HERE.    


61
00:05:42,276 --> 00:05:46,110
- CAREER ANXIETY?               
- OH, YOU HAVEN'T MET THE MAYOR.


62
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:49,247
    BUT, HEY, HE GIVES KILLER   
    CHRISTMAS PRESENTS--        


63
00:05:49,316 --> 00:05:52,017
        <i> AND I MEAN... KILLER.</i>  


64
00:05:52,085 --> 00:05:54,085
[ Groaning ] NO, NOT AGAIN!     


65
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:59,491
- IS THIS FOR<i> ME?</i>               
- GEEZ, JAROD, DON'T TELL ME... 


66
00:05:59,559 --> 00:06:01,860
    YOU NEVER GOT A CHRISTMAS   
    PRESENT BEFORE.             


67
00:06:01,928 --> 00:06:07,132
    NOT IN A VERY LONG TIME.    
    THANK YOU.                  


68
00:06:18,412 --> 00:06:20,579
A PASTRY WITH CANDIED CHERRIES. 


69
00:06:20,647 --> 00:06:22,813
IT'S FRUITCAKE.                 


70
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:26,551
            A CAKE WITH FRUIT   
            BAKED RIGHT IN.     


71
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:28,720
    THANK YOU.                  
    THIS HAS TO BE DELICIOUS.   


72
00:06:28,788 --> 00:06:32,591
<i>[ Woman On P.A. ]</i>               
<i>RECORDS DEPARTMENT, PLEASE</i>      
<i>CALL THE THIRD FLOOR.</i>           


73
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:36,861
SHOULD WE TELL HIM?             
            LET HIM DISCOVER IT.


74
00:06:36,929 --> 00:06:39,631
    YEAH.                       


75
00:06:39,699 --> 00:06:41,632
            MMM!                


76
00:06:41,701 --> 00:06:45,670
        ♪♪ [ Christmas Carol ]  


77
00:07:06,193 --> 00:07:09,227
        JAROD HAS BEEN MOVED    
        TO HIS ROOM.            


78
00:07:09,296 --> 00:07:12,664
    AS ALWAYS, I BEGIN MY       
    CHRISTMAS HIATUS TOMORROW.  


79
00:07:12,732 --> 00:07:14,799
    I'LL BE IN MOUNT PLEASANT   
    AT THE USUAL NUMBER.        


80
00:07:20,974 --> 00:07:22,974
    IT IS THE CHRISTMAS SEASON. 


81
00:07:23,043 --> 00:07:25,109
BUT THE TOWER DEEMS IT BEST     
TO INSULATE JAROD...            


82
00:07:25,178 --> 00:07:27,545
FROM THE TRAPPINGS              
OF POPULAR CULTURE.             


83
00:07:29,683 --> 00:07:32,450
            <i> [ Young Sydney ]</i>   
            <i> JAROD, I'LL BE GONE</i>
            <i> FOR THE WEEK,</i>      


84
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:34,485
            <i> AND I WANTED</i>       
            <i> TO SAY GOOD-BYE.</i>   


85
00:07:34,554 --> 00:07:37,622
WHY DO YOU GO AWAY EVERY YEAR   
WHEN IT TURNS COLD OUTSIDE?     


86
00:07:37,691 --> 00:07:40,492
    BUSINESS, JAROD. THAT'S ALL.


87
00:07:40,561 --> 00:07:42,794
IF YOU CAN KEEP A SECRET, I     
BROUGHT YOU A LITTLE SOMETHING. 


88
00:07:42,863 --> 00:07:45,964
                        A GIFT. 


89
00:07:46,032 --> 00:07:48,566
        A GIFT?                 


90
00:07:56,008 --> 00:07:59,477
        - THIS IS SNOW.         
        - YES. REMEMBER.        


91
00:07:59,545 --> 00:08:02,646
-TELL NO ONE I GAVE THIS TO YOU.
-TAKE ME OUTSIDE, SYDNEY.       


92
00:08:02,715 --> 00:08:05,816
    - TO SEE THE REAL SNOW.     
    - I CAN'T, JAROD.           


93
00:08:05,885 --> 00:08:09,420
BUT I WANT TO SEE IT            
FOR MYSELF.                     
            ENJOY THIS SNOW.    


94
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:11,422
            AND I WILL SEE YOU  
            AGAIN SOON.         


95
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,893
                        OKAY?   


96
00:08:24,037 --> 00:08:26,771
I GOT YOU!                      
            AAH!                


97
00:08:29,743 --> 00:08:32,376
[ Laughing ]                    


98
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:38,550
        [ Gasps, Screams ]      
        LET'S GET OUT OF HERE!  


99
00:08:38,618 --> 00:08:41,118
    [ Both Screaming ]          


100
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:48,392
TWO KIDS FOUND HER              
BURIED IN THE SNOW              
A COUPLE HOURS AGO.             


101
00:09:01,241 --> 00:09:04,175
<i>[ Guerra ]</i>                      
<i>NOW, THAT'S CRIMINAL.</i>           


102
00:09:04,243 --> 00:09:07,579
<i>VAGRANT. AFTER YOU THAW HER,</i>    
<i>CHECK FOR NEEDLE MARKS.</i>         


103
00:09:08,815 --> 00:09:11,582
<i>MY PRELIM IS OVERDOSE.</i>          


104
00:09:11,651 --> 00:09:14,085
    - I WONDER WHO SHE IS.      
    - WE'LL NEVER KNOW.         


105
00:09:14,154 --> 00:09:16,420
L.G.L.                          
BAG HER AND TAG HER.            


106
00:09:16,489 --> 00:09:19,290
AND NEXT TIME, PLEASE--         
DON'T MAKE ME WAIT.             


107
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:23,761
    - "L.G.L."?                 
    - LITTLE GIRL LOST.         


108
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:25,764
NO WITNESS, NO I.D.             


109
00:09:25,832 --> 00:09:29,567
HER FAMILY MUST BE WORRIED SICK,
WONDERING WHERE SHE IS.         


110
00:09:30,703 --> 00:09:32,837
THAT'S THE TRAGIC PART.         


111
00:09:32,906 --> 00:09:35,806
SHE'S PROBABLY A RUNAWAY.       
WE GET THEM ALL THE TIME.       


112
00:09:35,876 --> 00:09:39,443
<i>NOTHIN' TO GO ON, SO</i>            
<i>SHE BECOMES A CASE NUMBER.</i>      


113
00:09:39,512 --> 00:09:41,679
<i>LIKE ALL THE REST.</i>              


114
00:09:46,686 --> 00:09:50,822
        - ARE YOU OKAY?         
        - NO.                   


115
00:10:01,201 --> 00:10:03,935
    [ Electrical Crackling ]    


116
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:20,217
    FASCINATING, HMM? ONLY      
    ONE TWIN IS WIRED, BUT      
    THEY BOTH FEEL THE SHOCK.   


117
00:10:26,526 --> 00:10:28,459
I DON'T EVEN WANNA KNOW.        


118
00:10:30,263 --> 00:10:33,230
CLEANUP CREW JUST CAME IN       
FROM CLEVELAND.                 
                ANY LUCK?       


119
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,966
- JAROD'S LAST LIFE IN A BOX.   
- [ Chuckles ]                  


120
00:10:39,772 --> 00:10:42,706
    <i> YOU'RE THE SHRINK.</i>         
    <i> MAYBE YOU CAN FIGURE OUT</i>   
    <i> THEIR MEANING.</i>             


121
00:10:42,776 --> 00:10:45,009
JAROD'S TRYING                  
TO TELL ME SOMETHING.           


122
00:10:45,078 --> 00:10:48,880
    MAKES A GREAT GREETING CARD.
    BUT FACE FACTS, SYD.        


123
00:10:48,948 --> 00:10:51,248
    AT THIS RATE, YOUR BOY WON'T
    BE HOME FOR THE HOLIDAYS.   


124
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:56,487
MAYBE NOT, BUT...               
HE'LL CONTACT ME.               
HE HAS TO.                      


125
00:10:56,556 --> 00:11:00,925
    - WELL, IT IS CHRISTMAS.    
    - I WORRY ABOUT HIM.        


126
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:03,494
OUT THERE THIS TIME OF YEAR.    
                        <i> RELAX.</i> 


127
00:11:03,563 --> 00:11:07,932
HE'S PROBABLY HOLED UP          
IN WHOVILLE, EXPERIENCING       
THE GRINCH FOR THE FIRST TIME.  


128
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,034
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>                


129
00:11:58,318 --> 00:12:00,751
    WOULD YOU LIKE SOME?        
    IT'S CALLED FRUITCAKE.      


130
00:12:01,988 --> 00:12:04,989
FRUITCAKE?                      
I'M NOT THAT HOMELESS.          


131
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:07,124
WHAT, ARE YOU                   
WRITING A BOOK?                 


132
00:12:07,193 --> 00:12:09,627
            UM, NO, NOT EXACTLY.


133
00:12:10,964 --> 00:12:13,097
[ Sighs ]                       
        YOU MISS HIM, DON'T YOU?


134
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:17,302
WHO?                            
            GEORGE.             
            CHRISTMAS GEORGE.   


135
00:12:17,370 --> 00:12:20,071
YOU KNEW GEORGE?                
            I FEEL LIKE I DID.  


136
00:12:20,139 --> 00:12:22,273
GEORGE WAS                      
ALL THE FAMILY I HAD.           


137
00:12:22,341 --> 00:12:27,177
WELL, HE WAS ALL THE FAMILY     
A LOT OF PEOPLE HAD.            


138
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:31,349
    <i> THE CHILDREN</i>               
    <i> AT THE SHELTER MISS HIM.</i>   
<i>YEAH. FOSTER KIDS, RUNAWAYS--</i>   


139
00:12:31,418 --> 00:12:35,253
THEY KNEW THE REAL GEORGE.      
OH, EVERYBODY                   
THOUGHT HE WAS A BUM,           


140
00:12:35,321 --> 00:12:38,622
BECAUSE HE DIDN'T HAVE A HOME   
AND PANHANDLED TO GET BY.       


141
00:12:38,691 --> 00:12:41,859
BUT HE TOOK ALL THAT MONEY,     
AND ONE DAY A YEAR,             


142
00:12:41,928 --> 00:12:45,963
HE MADE SURE THEY HAD           
PRESENTS AND A SPECIAL MEAL.    


143
00:12:46,032 --> 00:12:49,167
EVERY CHRISTMAS EVE,            
HE'D DRESS AS SANTA...          


144
00:12:49,235 --> 00:12:52,203
AND READ TO                     
THOSE KIDS ALL NIGHT LONG.      


145
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:54,305
    THAT'S WHY THEY CALLED HIM  
    CHRISTMAS GEORGE.           


146
00:12:54,374 --> 00:12:57,809
YEAH.                           
WHEN GEORGE WAS ALIVE,          


147
00:12:57,878 --> 00:13:00,945
THEY ALL HAD FAMILY             
FOR AT LEAST ONE DAY.           


148
00:13:02,883 --> 00:13:06,017
CHRISTMAS DOESN'T COUNT         
FOR SQUAT WITHOUT FAMILY, SON.  


149
00:13:07,654 --> 00:13:09,687
                NO.             


150
00:13:09,755 --> 00:13:11,856
            I'M BEGINNING       
            TO REALIZE THAT.    


151
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:28,239
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>OH, THERE YOU ARE, JAROD.</i>       


152
00:13:28,308 --> 00:13:31,575
I JUST WANTED TO THANK YOU      
FOR ALL THE WORK YOU'VE DONE    
THIS SEASON.                    


153
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:34,912
    WITHOUT CHRISTMAS GEORGE,   
    IT HASN'T BEEN THE SAME.    


154
00:13:34,981 --> 00:13:38,016
OH, I'M HAPPY TO HELP.          


155
00:13:38,084 --> 00:13:40,284
            FOR A HAPPY MAN,    
            YOU LOOK PERPLEXED. 


156
00:13:40,353 --> 00:13:43,287
WELL, THE TRUTH IS, I AM.       


157
00:13:43,356 --> 00:13:46,423
- HAVE YOU READ THIS?           
-<i> [ Chuckles ]</i>                  
<i>  "THE NIGHT BEFORE CHRISTMAS"?</i> 


158
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:51,396
                IT'S A CLASSIC! 
IT'S VERY GOOD, BUT I'M A LITTLE
CONFUSED ABOUT SOMETHING.       


159
00:13:51,464 --> 00:13:55,132
NOW, IF SANTA CLAUS             
WERE TO DELIVER A PRESENT       
TO EVERY CHILD ON EARTH,        


160
00:13:55,201 --> 00:13:58,603
HE'D HAVE TO VISIT              
830 HOMES A SECOND.             


161
00:13:58,672 --> 00:14:02,172
WHICH WOULD MEAN HIS REINDEER   
WOULD HAVE TO TRAVEL            
ABOUT 700 MILES PER SECOND,     


162
00:14:02,241 --> 00:14:05,476
AND HE'D HAVE 1/1000th          
OF A SECOND TO PARK THE SLEIGH, 


163
00:14:05,545 --> 00:14:09,447
TO CRAWL DOWN THE CHIMNEY,      
TO PASS OUT THE PRESENTS        
AND TO EAT COOKIES AND MILK.    


164
00:14:09,516 --> 00:14:12,383
<i>AND FOR A MIDDLE-AGED,</i>          
<i>OVERWEIGHT MAN,</i>                 
<i>THAT'S QUITE A FEAT.</i>            


165
00:14:12,451 --> 00:14:15,719
        [ Chuckles ]            
        SANTA WORKS             
        IN MYSTERIOUS WAYS.     


166
00:14:15,788 --> 00:14:19,557
BUT IT'S SO FANTASTICAL.        
WHY WOULD ANYBODY BELIEVE IT?   


167
00:14:21,094 --> 00:14:24,895
        IT'S CHRISTMAS, JAROD.  
        ANYTHING'S POSSIBLE.    


168
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:29,066
OH.                             
                    [ Laughs ]  


169
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:46,250
ANGEL, THEY'RE GETTING READY    
TO STRING SOME POPCORN.         


170
00:14:46,319 --> 00:14:49,020
DON'T YOU WANT TO HELP?         


171
00:14:49,089 --> 00:14:51,189
DON'T YOU WANT                  
TO TALK TO SANTA?               


172
00:14:51,258 --> 00:14:54,325
                HE'S NOT SANTA. 
IS SOMETHING WRONG?             


173
00:14:54,394 --> 00:14:57,328
            IS CHRISTMAS GEORGE 
            COMING BACK?        


174
00:14:59,232 --> 00:15:01,399
    NO. NO, HE ISN'T.           


175
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:03,901
                WHY NOT?        


176
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:06,737
CHRISTMAS GEORGE DIED.          


177
00:15:07,807 --> 00:15:10,074
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?    


178
00:15:10,143 --> 00:15:13,144
    WE WON'T EVER SEE HIM AGAIN.


179
00:15:13,212 --> 00:15:16,747
WELL, THAT'S TRUE,              
AND THEN AGAIN, IT ISN'T.       


180
00:15:16,816 --> 00:15:19,016
COULD I ASK YOU SOMETHING?      


181
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:21,219
WHY DID YOU                     
LIKE CHRISTMAS GEORGE?          


182
00:15:25,659 --> 00:15:28,126
        SOMETHING UNDER THE TREE
        ON CHRISTMAS.           


183
00:15:28,194 --> 00:15:33,798
SO WHAT YOU'RE SAYING IS THAT   
HE HAD A SPIRIT, A FEELING,     
THAT MADE YOU FEEL GOOD.        


184
00:15:33,866 --> 00:15:39,704
WELL, AS LONG AS YOU HAVE       
THAT FEELING, CHRISTMAS GEORGE  
IS GONNA BE RIGHT HERE.         


185
00:15:41,908 --> 00:15:45,876
SO EVERY TIME IT'S CHRISTMAS,   
I CAN THINK ABOUT GEORGE,       
AND HE'LL BE HERE?              


186
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:48,012
    EVERY TIME.                 


187
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:53,485
[ Chuckles ]                    


188
00:15:55,589 --> 00:15:57,856
CAN I HELP?                     
<i>[ Boy ]</i>                         
<i>SURE. COME ON.</i>                  


189
00:16:07,534 --> 00:16:10,902
<i>♪♪ [ Violin:</i>                    
<i>    "O Holy Night" ]</i>            


190
00:16:45,238 --> 00:16:48,573
<i>♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>                


191
00:17:09,362 --> 00:17:12,296
<i>[ Dr. Fugimora ]</i>                
<i>GEEZ, JAROD.</i>                    
<i>YOU'VE RUN 137 TESTS.</i>           


192
00:17:12,365 --> 00:17:14,465
<i>ANY LUCK ON THE L.G.L.?</i>         


193
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:18,002
    - THAT'S NOT HER NAME.      
    - I DIDN'T MEAN ANYTHING.   


194
00:17:19,739 --> 00:17:23,841
    SHE SHOULD HAVE A REAL NAME.
    HER FAMILY SHOULD KNOW.     


195
00:17:23,910 --> 00:17:26,377
        ESPECIALLY AT           
        THIS TIME OF THE YEAR.  


196
00:17:26,446 --> 00:17:28,746
        YOU'RE NOT GONNA        
        GIVE UP, ARE YOU?       


197
00:17:32,985 --> 00:17:36,187
<i>[ Male Deejay ]</i>                 
<i>AND WE'VE GOT MORE CHRISTMAS</i>    
<i>HITS COMING YOUR WAY, SO...</i>     


198
00:17:36,256 --> 00:17:38,322
<i>SNUGGLE UP BY THE FIRE</i>          
<i>WITH THAT SPECIAL SOMEONE...</i>    


199
00:17:38,391 --> 00:17:40,725
<i>AND ENJOY THE HOLIDAY SEASON.</i>   


200
00:18:16,596 --> 00:18:18,529
                    [ Ringing ] 


201
00:18:18,598 --> 00:18:21,265
            WHAT?               
    [ Man ]                     
    IT'S ME.                    


202
00:18:21,334 --> 00:18:24,202
I'M HAVING A HOLIDAY            
GATHERING AT THE CLUB.          


203
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,670
IT WOULDN'T BE THE SAME         
WITHOUT MY FAVORITE GIRL.       


204
00:18:26,739 --> 00:18:29,941
        I'LL BE THERE.          
VERY WELL.                      
CHRISTMAS EVE AT 7:00.          


205
00:18:30,009 --> 00:18:35,713
SOME EUROPEAN ASSOCIATES        
WILL ATTEND. BE PROMPT.         
OF COURSE, DADDY.               


206
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:37,848
        MERRY CHRIST--          
[ Line Disconnects ]            


207
00:18:40,387 --> 00:18:42,387
    [ Beeps ]                   


208
00:19:07,781 --> 00:19:10,781
<i>[ Woman On P.A., Indistinct ]</i>   


209
00:19:17,657 --> 00:19:21,759
    GUNSHOT WOUND TO THE GILL?  
[ Laughs ]                      
NOT A PATIENT.                  


210
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:24,995
LUNCH.                          
    AREN'T YOU A LITTLE YOUNG   
    FOR POISON FISH?            


211
00:19:25,064 --> 00:19:28,632
PUFFER FISH IS ONLY POISON      
BEFORE IT'S PREPARED.           
                    <i> KIM.</i>       


212
00:19:28,701 --> 00:19:32,469
        FUGU TOXIN IS 500 TIMES 
        STRONGER THAN CYANIDE.  
<i>YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.</i>               


213
00:19:32,538 --> 00:19:35,706
BUT WHEN IT'S DONE RIGHT,       
ALL YOU GET ARE TINGLY TOES     
AND A GREAT BUZZ.               


214
00:19:35,775 --> 00:19:39,176
CHRISTMAS DINNER AROUND HERE.   
MY FUGU'S A TRADITION.          


215
00:19:39,245 --> 00:19:41,812
THE BOYS IN THE MORGUE          
LOVE IT.                        


216
00:19:41,881 --> 00:19:44,548
AND IT GOES GREAT               
WITH CRANBERRIES.               


217
00:19:44,617 --> 00:19:47,051
    <i> I'LL STICK WITH FRUITCAKE.</i> 


218
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:50,888
<i>AND RELAX. MY UNCLE WAS</i>         
<i>A MASTER FUGU CHEF IN TOKYO.</i>    


219
00:19:50,957 --> 00:19:53,824
        - WAS?                  
        - HE'S RETIRED.         


220
00:19:53,893 --> 00:19:57,294
    [ Laughs ] OH, GOOD. WELL,  
    I'M GLAD TO HEAR THAT.      


221
00:19:57,363 --> 00:20:00,163
            UH, WOULD YOU       
            HELP ME WITH THIS?  
MAN, DID YOU SPILL A WHOLE MUG? 


222
00:20:00,232 --> 00:20:02,399
        WELL, ACTUALLY,         
        I SPILLED A WHOLE POT.  


223
00:20:02,468 --> 00:20:04,302
I'LL GET YOU A DUPLICATE.       
                <i> OH, NO, NO, NO.</i>
                <i> THAT'S OKAY.</i>   


224
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:07,504
            JUST SHOW ME WHERE  
            THE OLD FILES ARE.  


225
00:20:30,463 --> 00:20:33,364
<i>[ Chattering, Phones Ringing ]</i>  
<i>[ Woman ] YES, IT SHOULD</i>        
<i>TAKE A FEW SECONDS...</i>           


226
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:35,366
<i>TO START WORKING.</i>               


227
00:20:35,435 --> 00:20:38,002
    YES, I'VE ALREADY           
    DISPATCHED THE AMBULANCE.   


228
00:20:38,071 --> 00:20:40,871
        <i> MA'AM-- MA'AM! NO.</i>     


229
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:44,108
        AN OVERFLOWING TOILET   
        IS NOT A 911 CALL.      


230
00:20:44,177 --> 00:20:47,578
     MA'AM. WOULD YOU PLEASE    
     HANG UP AND CALL A PLUMBER?


231
00:20:47,646 --> 00:20:53,451
    [ Speaking With Mouth Full ]
    OKAY. YOU NEED TO...        
    INDUCE VOMITING.            


232
00:20:53,519 --> 00:20:57,554
            YES. UH, NO, YOUR   
            FINGER WILL BE FINE.


233
00:20:57,623 --> 00:21:00,491
                        <i> YES.</i>   
    [ Man ] IT'S NOT WORKING.   
    IT'S NOT WORKING.           


234
00:21:00,559 --> 00:21:03,594
YOUR SON IS GOING TO BE         
FINE, MR. HODGES, IF YOU        
JUST LISTEN CAREFULLY.          


235
00:21:03,662 --> 00:21:06,597
<i>OKAY.</i>                           
<i>[ Jarod ] NOW, REMEMBER,</i>        
<i>CLEAR THE AIRWAY...</i>             


236
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:09,867
<i>AND TILT HIS HEAD BACK.</i>         
    <i> RIGHT. TILT HIS HEAD BACK.</i> 


237
00:21:09,936 --> 00:21:12,569
<i>NOW BACK TO THE BREATHING.</i>      
        <i> OKAY.</i>                  


238
00:21:12,638 --> 00:21:15,106
[ Beeping ]                     


239
00:21:15,175 --> 00:21:18,509
<i>[ Hodges ] OKAY.</i>                
<i>NOW CONTINUE THE UP AND DOWN</i>    
<i>MOTION ON HIS CHEST.</i>            


240
00:21:18,577 --> 00:21:22,379
<i>OKAY. FIVE-COUNT?</i>               
<i>YES.</i>                            


241
00:21:22,448 --> 00:21:24,415
[ Beeping ]                     
<i>[ Hodges ]</i>                      
<i>OH, MY GOD. HE'S BREATHING!</i>     


242
00:21:24,484 --> 00:21:26,884
-<i> MY SON IS BREATHING!</i>          
- THAT'S FANTASTIC, MR. HODGES. 


243
00:21:26,953 --> 00:21:28,953
    THEY'RE HERE!               
    THE AMBULANCE JUST GOT HERE.


244
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:31,889
<i>YOU SEE?</i>                        
<i>THAT WASN'T SO DIFFICULT.</i>       


245
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:34,258
MERRY CHRISTMAS.                
        THANK YOU SO MUCH.      
         THANK YOU.             


246
00:21:45,237 --> 00:21:47,604
    <i> - [ Woman On Tape ]</i>        
     <i>  911 OPERATOR.</i>            
    <i> - HELLO. MY NAME'S HARRY.</i>  


247
00:21:47,673 --> 00:21:50,074
<i>I'M CALLING FROM THE CORNER</i>     
<i>OF LAWSON AND HILL.</i>             


248
00:21:50,143 --> 00:21:53,844
<i>MY FRIEND-- OH, GOD,</i>            
<i>MY FRIEND GEORGE IS--</i>           


249
00:21:53,912 --> 00:21:57,415
<i>[ Woman ] TELL ME WHAT</i>          
<i>THE PROBLEM IS, SIR.</i>            
<i>THEY RAN GEORGE DOWN.</i>           


250
00:21:57,483 --> 00:21:59,984
    YOU GOTTA GET SOMEBODY      
    DOWN HERE. LAWSON AND HILL. 


251
00:22:00,052 --> 00:22:02,652
    RIGHT IN FRONT              
    OF THE CHILDREN'S SHELTER.  


252
00:22:02,721 --> 00:22:04,788
    HURRY. YOU GOTTA HURRY.     
[ Operator ]                    
I'M CALLING IT IN, SIR.         


253
00:22:04,857 --> 00:22:07,825
IS ANYONE ELSE HURT?            
    NO, THEY JUST HIT HIM,      
    AND THEY LEFT.              


254
00:22:07,893 --> 00:22:10,694
    I DIDN'T SEE NO CAR.        


255
00:22:16,502 --> 00:22:20,037
- THIS IS WHERE IT HAPPENED?    
-<i> WHERE I FOUND HIM.</i>            


256
00:22:20,106 --> 00:22:23,540
        THEY JUST LEFT GEORGE   
        THERE TO DIE.           


257
00:22:23,609 --> 00:22:27,812
    - "THEY"?                   
    - I DON'T KNOW.             
      CRASH WOKE ME UP.         


258
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,880
    I DIDN'T SEE IT.            


259
00:22:32,518 --> 00:22:34,852
                    I'M SORRY.  


260
00:22:34,921 --> 00:22:39,890
I NEVER LEFT HIS SIDE.          
NEVER. NOT UNTIL THE CORONER    
SHOWED UP.                      


261
00:22:41,127 --> 00:22:43,593
            THE CORONER?        
[ Sniffles ]                    


262
00:22:43,662 --> 00:22:46,297
        NOT THE POLICE?         


263
00:22:46,365 --> 00:22:50,000
BETTER DIRECTIONS, I GUESS.     


264
00:22:50,069 --> 00:22:54,738
[ Sighs ]                       
YOU KNOW,                       
HE HELD MY HAND, AND--          


265
00:22:56,309 --> 00:22:59,743
AND WE GOT TO SAY GOOD-BYE.     


266
00:22:59,812 --> 00:23:02,146
        YOU MEAN, HE DIDN'T     
        DIE INSTANTLY?          


267
00:23:02,215 --> 00:23:05,583
AH, HELL NO.                    
HE WAS A FIGHTER.               


268
00:23:05,651 --> 00:23:07,751
CORONER TRIED TO SAVE HIM.      


269
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:10,754
GAVE GEORGE A SHOT              
AND EVERYTHING, BUT--           


270
00:23:10,823 --> 00:23:13,123
DIDN'T HELP.                    


271
00:23:13,192 --> 00:23:15,593
I NEVER KNEW CORONERS           
CARRIED DOCTOR BAGS.            


272
00:23:15,661 --> 00:23:18,963
            NEITHER DID I.      


273
00:23:19,032 --> 00:23:22,332
SHE DID WHAT SHE COULD,         
I GUESS. BUT BY THE TIME        
THE COPS GOT HERE,              


274
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:24,869
SHE TOLD THEM                   
GEORGE HAD PASSED.              
                    SHE?        


275
00:23:26,739 --> 00:23:29,273
                WAS SHE ALONE?  
        YEP.                    


276
00:23:30,977 --> 00:23:36,714
        AND SHE HAD RED HAIR.   
    UH, YEAH.                   


277
00:23:36,783 --> 00:23:38,849
HOW'D YOU KNOW?                 


278
00:23:42,021 --> 00:23:44,822
<i>[ Woman On P.A. ]</i>               
<i>ANY AVAILABLE ASSISTANCE</i>        
<i>TO THE I.V. UNIT.</i>               


279
00:23:46,526 --> 00:23:50,027
WHY HAVEN'T YOU SHIPPED         
THE L.G.L.? WE NEED             
SLAB SPACE FOR THE HOLIDAYS.    


280
00:23:51,663 --> 00:23:54,631
        I FOUND STRESS FRACTURES
        IN HER LEGS.            
FORGET ABOUT IT.                


281
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:57,168
WE'VE DONE OUR DUE DILIGENCE.   


282
00:23:57,236 --> 00:24:00,370
FINISH UP THE PAPERWORK         
AND SEND HER ALONG.             
            I UNDERSTAND.       


283
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:03,740
BY THE WAY, NEW GUY             
WORKS CHRISTMAS EVE.            


284
00:24:03,809 --> 00:24:09,447
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT. LAST YEAR 
WAS SO SLOW, WE BROKE OUT       
A BOTTLE OF CHRISTMAS CHEER.    


285
00:24:09,515 --> 00:24:12,115
TOO BAD I WON'T BE HERE         
WITH YOU TO SHARE A TOAST.      


286
00:24:15,020 --> 00:24:18,923
WELL, YOU NEVER KNOW, DOCTOR.   
CHRISTMAS HAS ITS WAY OF        
BRINGING PEOPLE TOGETHER.       


287
00:24:29,535 --> 00:24:33,904
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>OUR JANE DOE'S REAL NAME</i>        
<i>IS GABRIELLE.</i>                   


288
00:24:33,973 --> 00:24:36,173
        GABRIELLE RYAN.         


289
00:24:36,242 --> 00:24:39,843
<i>SHE'S FROM NASHTON.</i>             
<i>SHE WOULD HAVE BEEN 18</i>          
<i>NEXT MONTH.</i>                     


290
00:24:39,912 --> 00:24:41,979
            HOW'D YOU DO THIS?  


291
00:24:42,048 --> 00:24:45,049
LOWER TIBIAL FRACTURES          
TO THE MEDIAL MALLEOLI.         


292
00:24:45,117 --> 00:24:48,318
                MEDIA WHO?      
    BAD ANKLES.                 


293
00:24:48,387 --> 00:24:51,655
<i>FROM COMPRESSION IMPACTS.</i>       


294
00:24:51,724 --> 00:24:54,124
THAT, AND SHE HAD CALLOUS       
PATTERNS ON HER HANDS LIKE THIS.


295
00:24:54,193 --> 00:24:56,994
<i>PARALLEL BARS WERE</i>              
<i>HER SPECIALTY.</i>                  


296
00:24:57,063 --> 00:24:59,329
WILL YOU TELL HER FAMILY        
RIGHT AWAY?                     


297
00:24:59,398 --> 00:25:01,399
        COUNT ON IT.            


298
00:25:02,902 --> 00:25:06,403
    HEY. GOOD WORK, JAROD.      


299
00:25:07,406 --> 00:25:09,406
            <i> SEE YOU AROUND.</i>    


300
00:25:11,611 --> 00:25:15,178
<i>[ Women's Choir ]</i>               
<i>♪ THIS POOR YOUNGLING ♪</i>         


301
00:25:15,248 --> 00:25:18,782
<i>♪ FOR WHOM WE DO SING ♪</i>         


302
00:25:20,119 --> 00:25:26,089
<i>♪ BY BY, LULLY, LULLAY ♪</i>        


303
00:25:29,428 --> 00:25:32,430
<i>♪ LULLY, LULLAY ♪</i>               


304
00:25:32,498 --> 00:25:36,800
<i>♪ THOU LITTLE TINY CHILD ♪</i>      


305
00:25:36,869 --> 00:25:42,506
<i>♪ BY BY LULLY, LULLAY ♪</i>         


306
00:25:43,709 --> 00:25:47,711
<i>♪ LULLAY, THOU LITTLE ♪</i>         


307
00:25:47,780 --> 00:25:50,381
<i>♪ TINY CHILD ♪</i>                  


308
00:25:50,450 --> 00:25:53,584
        FACE IT, SYDNEY.        
        IT'S ALMOST CHRISTMAS.  
<i>♪ BY BY LULLY ♪</i>                 


309
00:25:53,653 --> 00:25:56,086
        HE'S NOT GOING TO CALL. 
<i>♪ LULLAY ♪</i>                      


310
00:25:56,155 --> 00:26:00,691
        [ Sighs ] I SEE YOU'RE  
        CLEARING OUT FOR YOUR   
        USUAL HOLIDAY HIATUS,   


311
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:04,228
                SO, HERE.       


312
00:26:04,297 --> 00:26:07,464
A CHRISTMAS PRESENT?            
FROM YOU?                       


313
00:26:08,867 --> 00:26:11,201
    DON'T GO HANGING MISTLETOE. 


314
00:26:13,272 --> 00:26:15,272
        SEE YOU AFTER THE FIRST.


315
00:26:19,078 --> 00:26:21,745
AND A MERRY CHRISTMAS           
TO YOU TOO, MISS PARKER.        


316
00:26:21,814 --> 00:26:27,551
<i>♪ BY BY, LULLY, LULLAY ♪♪</i>       


317
00:26:29,988 --> 00:26:32,089
                    KIM.        
            HEY.                


318
00:26:32,158 --> 00:26:34,958
        HI. I WAS GOING OVER    
        LAST YEAR'S DUTY ROSTER,


319
00:26:35,027 --> 00:26:37,895
    AND I SEE THAT YOU WERE     
    WORKING ON CHRISTMAS EVE.   


320
00:26:37,963 --> 00:26:42,332
I WAS THE ROOKIE LAST YEAR.     
THAT MEANS THAT THIS YEAR,      
<i>YOU</i> GET TO WAIT UP FOR SANTA.   


321
00:26:42,401 --> 00:26:45,536
        [ Laughs ] I DON'T MIND 
        WORKING THE HOLIDAY.    


322
00:26:45,605 --> 00:26:47,738
THE TRUTH IS, I'VE NEVER        
REALLY HAD CHRISTMAS EVE OFF.   


323
00:26:47,806 --> 00:26:51,641
    I WANTED TO ASK YOU         
    ABOUT THE AUTOPSIES THAT    
    WERE PERFORMED THAT NIGHT.  


324
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:54,612
SHOOT.                          
        ACCORDING TO THE FILES, 
        THERE WERE ONLY TWO.    


325
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:59,082
        A HOMELESS HIT-AND-RUN  
        VICTIM NAMED CHRISTMAS  
        GEORGE,                 


326
00:26:59,151 --> 00:27:01,685
        AND AN 80-YEAR-OLD WOMAN
        NAMED EDWINA MORRIS.    


327
00:27:01,754 --> 00:27:04,655
        DO YOU REMEMBER THEM?   
I REMEMBER                      
THE MORRIS WOMAN.               


328
00:27:04,724 --> 00:27:08,592
DEAD RINGER FOR                 
GRANDMA WALTON. ONLY FAT.       


329
00:27:08,661 --> 00:27:10,994
BUT I REALLY WASN'T INVOLVED    
IN THE HIT-AND-RUN.             


330
00:27:11,064 --> 00:27:13,130
            I THOUGHT YOU       
            WERE THE ONLY ONE   
            ON DUTY THAT NIGHT. 


331
00:27:13,199 --> 00:27:15,532
I WAS, UNTIL DRAKE              
CAME IN WITH THE HIT-AND-RUN.   


332
00:27:15,601 --> 00:27:17,535
SHE DID THAT AUTOPSY.           


333
00:27:17,603 --> 00:27:20,804
    THE CHIEF CORONER CAME IN   
    ON CHRISTMAS EVE...         


334
00:27:20,872 --> 00:27:23,874
        TO PERFORM AN AUTOPSY   
        ON A HOMELESS MAN?      


335
00:27:23,943 --> 00:27:27,611
WITH KARMA LIKE HERS,           
SHE'S PROBABLY NOT THAT POPULAR 
ON THE PARTY CIRCUIT,           


336
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:30,747
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYIN'.    


337
00:27:30,816 --> 00:27:33,617
                THE OTHER BODY. 
                EDWINA MORRIS.  


338
00:27:33,686 --> 00:27:35,652
        WAS SHE A PSYCH PATIENT?
NO.                             


339
00:27:35,721 --> 00:27:38,922
JUST A VERY LARGE               
GRANDMOTHER OF SIX...           


340
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:41,291
WHO DIED OF NATURAL CAUSES.     


341
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:44,194
WHY?                            
        ACCORDING TO            
        THE TOXICOLOGY REPORT,  


342
00:27:44,263 --> 00:27:46,663
    THERE WERE TRACES OF        
    PHENOTRIPTICOL IN HER BLOOD.


343
00:27:46,732 --> 00:27:48,632
    - PHENOTRIPTICOL?           
    - YES.                      


344
00:27:48,701 --> 00:27:51,735
ISN'T THAT USED                 
TO SUBDUE PATIENTS              
DURING PSYCHOTIC EPISODES?      


345
00:27:51,803 --> 00:27:54,638
AND IN STRONGER DOSES, IT       
INDUCES A STATE OF PARALYSIS,   


346
00:27:54,706 --> 00:27:58,242
<i>WHERE THE PATIENT IS CONSCIOUS,</i> 
<i>BUT RENDERED IMMOBILE.</i>          


347
00:27:58,310 --> 00:28:03,047
    - DEAD. BUT NOT DEAD.       
    - OH, MY GOD.               


348
00:28:03,115 --> 00:28:07,084
PLEASE DON'T TELL ME THAT       
I PERFORMED AN AUTOPSY ON       
SOMEONE WHO WAS ALIVE--         


349
00:28:07,152 --> 00:28:10,387
        - AND CONSCIOUS!        
        - NO. NO.               


350
00:28:10,456 --> 00:28:13,757
    - YOU DIDN'T.               
    - WELL, THIS COULDN'T       
      HAVE HAPPENED.            


351
00:28:13,825 --> 00:28:17,494
SOMEONE MUST HAVE MESSED UP     
THE TOXICOLOGY REPORTS.         


352
00:28:17,563 --> 00:28:21,332
        OR SWITCHED THEM.       
        ON PURPOSE.             


353
00:28:23,902 --> 00:28:26,836
<i>[ Women's Choir On Radio ]</i>      
<i>♪ WHAT CHILD IS THIS ♪</i>          


354
00:28:26,905 --> 00:28:28,838
<i>♪ WHO LAID TO REST ♪</i>            


355
00:28:28,908 --> 00:28:33,576
<i>♪ ON MARY'S LAP IS SLEEPING ♪</i>   


356
00:28:33,645 --> 00:28:38,415
<i>♪ WHOM ANGELS GREET</i>             
<i>  WITH ANTHEMS SWEET ♪</i>          


357
00:28:38,483 --> 00:28:43,553
<i>♪ WHILE SHEPHERDS WATCH</i>         
<i>  ARE KEEPING ♪</i>                 


358
00:28:43,622 --> 00:28:48,091
<i>♪ THIS, THIS, IS</i>                
<i>  CHRIST THE KING ♪</i>             


359
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:53,463
<i>♪ WHOM SHEPHERDS GUARD</i>          
<i>  AND ANGELS SING ♪</i>             


360
00:28:53,532 --> 00:28:57,901
<i>♪ HASTE, HASTE</i>                  
<i>  TO BRING HIM LAUD ♪</i>           


361
00:28:57,970 --> 00:29:02,973
<i>♪ THE BABE, THE SON OF MARY ♪♪</i>  


362
00:29:20,258 --> 00:29:24,862
YOU'RE MISS PARKER, AREN'T YOU? 
            I DIDN'T KNOW       
            ANYONE WAS HERE.    


363
00:29:24,930 --> 00:29:27,430
            PLEASE DON'T TELL   
            ANYONE I WAS HERE.  
NO, WAIT.                       


364
00:29:29,401 --> 00:29:32,469
WHY DID YOU COME?               


365
00:29:32,538 --> 00:29:36,540
MY MOM LETS ME SEE THE RABBITS  
WHEN NO ONE'S HERE.             


366
00:29:36,609 --> 00:29:39,576
I WANT ONE, BUT MY FATHER       
WON'T LET ME HAVE PETS AT HOME. 


367
00:29:39,645 --> 00:29:41,978
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>                 
<i>WE'VE BEEN STUDYING THEM.</i>       


368
00:29:42,047 --> 00:29:44,414
<i>THERE ARE THREE SETS OF TWINS.</i>  


369
00:29:44,483 --> 00:29:48,318
NOW WATCH. THEY'VE NEVER        
BEEN TOGETHER BEFORE.           


370
00:29:48,387 --> 00:29:53,390
BUT SOMEHOW, THE ONES THAT      
ARE GENETICALLY IDENTICAL       
JUST SEEM TO FIND EACH OTHER.   


371
00:29:55,094 --> 00:30:00,197
LIKE SOMETHING INSIDE THEM      
DRAWS THEM TOGETHER. SEE?       


372
00:30:00,266 --> 00:30:03,100
THEY'RE SOFT.                   


373
00:30:16,315 --> 00:30:18,782
         [ Door Latch Rattling ]


374
00:31:02,594 --> 00:31:04,594
<i>[ Car Alarm Beeping ]</i>           


375
00:31:08,566 --> 00:31:12,368
    - EXCUSE ME. CAN YOU SP--   
    - NOT MY NEIGHBORHOOD.      


376
00:31:12,437 --> 00:31:14,370
            [ Starting Engine ] 


377
00:31:14,439 --> 00:31:16,839
        [ Engaging Gears ]      


378
00:31:21,446 --> 00:31:24,113
        - [ Screams ]           
        - [ Grunts ]            


379
00:31:36,294 --> 00:31:39,529
OH, MY GOD.                     
DIDN'T YOU SEE ME?              
JAROD!                          


380
00:31:39,598 --> 00:31:43,966
    [ Grunting ] I'M OKAY.      
    I'M OKAY. IT WAS JUST A--   
    A LITTLE SCRATCH.           


381
00:31:44,035 --> 00:31:47,470
                ARE<i> YOU</i> OKAY?   
I'M FINE. COME ON.              


382
00:31:47,539 --> 00:31:49,672
I-I CAN HELP YOU OUT            
WITH THAT.                      


383
00:31:53,779 --> 00:31:57,247
                    [ Panting ] 
<i>YOU CERTAINLY COME PREPARED.</i>    


384
00:31:57,315 --> 00:32:00,783
OUR PATIENTS MAY BE DEAD,       
BUT WE'RE STILL DOCTORS, RIGHT? 


385
00:32:00,852 --> 00:32:03,987
I SUPPOSE.                      
    <i> I ALWAYS KEEP IT ON HAND.</i>  


386
00:32:04,055 --> 00:32:06,822
            YOU NEVER KNOW WHEN 
            SOMEBODY MIGHT NEED 
            ONE OF US.          


387
00:32:06,891 --> 00:32:08,892
    YOU NEVER KNOW.             


388
00:32:17,168 --> 00:32:19,202
    -<i> [ Beeps ]</i>                 
    - [ Whirring ]              


389
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:33,383
WHY, JAROD. I THOUGHT THEY'D    
TAKEN YOU BACK TO YOUR ROOM.    


390
00:32:33,452 --> 00:32:36,719
    - WHAT ARE THOSE, SYDNEY?   
    - THEY'RE ANOTHER PROJECT   
      I'M WORKING ON.           


391
00:32:36,788 --> 00:32:38,854
[ Buzzing ]                     
[ Woman ] YOUR CAR              
IS READY TO TAKE YOU...         


392
00:32:38,923 --> 00:32:42,792
- TO THE MOUNT PLEASANT HOME.   
- YES. THANK YOU. TELL THEM     
  TO WAIT.                      


393
00:32:42,861 --> 00:32:46,295
             [ Young Jarod ]    
             YOU WILL COME BACK,
             WON'T YOU, SYDNEY? 


394
00:32:46,365 --> 00:32:48,998
[ Young Sydney ]                
I ALWAYS COME BACK, JAROD.      
DON'T I?                        


395
00:32:50,001 --> 00:32:53,069
[ Whirring ]                    


396
00:32:53,138 --> 00:32:55,705
[ Woman ]                       
YOUR CAR IS READY TO TAKE YOU   
TO THE MOUNT PLEASANT HOME.     


397
00:32:55,773 --> 00:32:57,874
YES, THANK YOU.                 


398
00:32:57,942 --> 00:32:59,875
...TAKE YOU TO                  
THE MOUNT PLEASANT HOME.        


399
00:32:59,944 --> 00:33:02,278
                [ Beeps ]       


400
00:33:06,851 --> 00:33:09,518
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>YOUR CAR IS READY TO TAKE YOU</i>   
<i>TO THE MOUNT PLEASANT HOME.</i>     


401
00:33:09,587 --> 00:33:11,921
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.            


402
00:34:00,305 --> 00:34:04,407
<i>♪♪ [ Big Band: "God Rest</i>        
<i>     You Merry, Gentlemen" ]</i>    


403
00:34:24,763 --> 00:34:28,197
<i>[ Line Ringing ]</i>                


404
00:34:30,168 --> 00:34:34,070
    LAST MINUTE GIFTS?          
    I NEED A LAST MINUTE GIFT.  


405
00:34:51,289 --> 00:34:54,590
            DR. FUGIMORA?       


406
00:34:54,659 --> 00:34:57,059
    <i> WELL, I HATE TO BE</i>         
    <i> THE BEARER OF BAD TIDINGS,</i> 


407
00:34:57,128 --> 00:35:01,397
        BUT YOU'RE GOING TO NEED
        TO COME TO WORK TODAY.  


408
00:35:01,466 --> 00:35:05,968
SOMETHING TERRIBLE HAS HAPPENED.
I'LL EXPLAIN EVERYTHING         
WHEN YOU GET THERE.             


409
00:35:08,139 --> 00:35:10,472
<i>DON'T YOU LOVE CHRISTMAS?</i>       


410
00:35:10,542 --> 00:35:14,143
    - IT'S SO CHRISTMASY.       
    - JAROD, I THOUGHT          
      YOU WERE WORKING TODAY.   


411
00:35:14,212 --> 00:35:16,179
        I AM.                   


412
00:35:16,247 --> 00:35:18,214
BUT I WANTED TO GIVE YOU        
A LITTLE SOMETHING.             


413
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:20,783
                FOR ME?         
MM-HMM.                         


414
00:35:22,654 --> 00:35:24,587
OPEN IT.                        


415
00:35:24,656 --> 00:35:28,257
            [ Sighs, Scoffs ]   
            FRUITCAKE.          


416
00:35:28,326 --> 00:35:30,994
    [ Sniffs ]                  
    THIS ACTUALLY SMELLS GOOD.  


417
00:35:31,062 --> 00:35:33,429
I WAS SO IMPRESSED WITH         
THE MAYOR'S GIFT, I TRIED       
BAKING ONE MYSELF,              


418
00:35:33,497 --> 00:35:35,431
AND I WANT YOU TO BE            
THE FIRST TO TASTE IT.          


419
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:38,934
                [ Sighs ]       


420
00:35:40,672 --> 00:35:42,805
                    MMM?        
OH, NO, THANK YOU.              


421
00:35:44,609 --> 00:35:49,345
            MMM. MMM!           


422
00:35:49,414 --> 00:35:52,582
            IT'S ACTUALLY GOOD. 


423
00:35:52,650 --> 00:35:56,285
        SO, UM, ARE YOU         
        GONNA SEE YOUR FAMILY   
        FOR THE HOLIDAYS?       


424
00:35:56,354 --> 00:35:59,322
I DON'T THINK THAT'S            
GOING TO BE POSSIBLE            
THIS YEAR.                      


425
00:36:02,059 --> 00:36:05,294
ARE YOU OKAY?                   


426
00:36:05,362 --> 00:36:07,863
        I... FEEL A LITTLE--    


427
00:36:09,667 --> 00:36:11,867
                MY GOD!         
                [ Retching ]    


428
00:36:11,937 --> 00:36:15,871
            DR. DRAKE?          
            LET ME HELP YOU.    


429
00:36:17,508 --> 00:36:19,942
        [ Gasping, Groaning ]   


430
00:36:21,779 --> 00:36:25,481
            MY STOMACH! MY GOD! 
            [ Gasping ]         


431
00:36:25,550 --> 00:36:29,118
        WHAT WAS IN THAT CAKE?  
I WENT TO GREAT PAINS           
MAKING THAT CAKE.               


432
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:31,554
IT COULDN'T HAVE POSSIBLY       
BEEN THE--                      
                        WHAT?   


433
00:36:31,622 --> 00:36:34,524
UH-OH.                          
                WHAT?           


434
00:36:34,593 --> 00:36:38,160
WELL, FUGIMORA HAS BEEN         
TEACHING ME HOW TO PREPARE      
PUFFER FISH.                    


435
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:40,996
AND I WAS PRACTICING WHEN       
I WAS MAKING THE FRUITCAKE.     


436
00:36:41,065 --> 00:36:44,467
    AND SOME OF IT MIGHT        
    HAVE ACCIDENTALLY SLIPPED   
    INTO THE BATTER.            


437
00:36:44,536 --> 00:36:46,469
                <i> PUFFER FISH?</i>   
        I'M AFRAID SO.          


438
00:36:46,537 --> 00:36:50,172
            YOU IDIOT!          
             YOU POISONED ME!   


439
00:36:50,241 --> 00:36:52,575
            [ Grunting In Pain ]
I'M SORRY.                      


440
00:36:52,644 --> 00:36:56,946
        - CALL 911.             
        - OKAY.                 


441
00:36:57,015 --> 00:37:00,482
    -<i> [ Cell Phone Beeping ]</i>    
    - UH--                      


442
00:37:00,552 --> 00:37:02,885
I CAN'T.                        
            JAROD,              
            WHAT ARE YOU DOING? 


443
00:37:04,922 --> 00:37:07,924
    - I CAN'T CALL 911.         
    - ARE YOU<i> CRAZY?</i>            


444
00:37:07,993 --> 00:37:09,925
<i>NO, BUT I AM THOROUGH.</i>          


445
00:37:09,994 --> 00:37:14,030
    IF I CALL 911,              
    THEY'D BE ABLE TO HELP YOU. 
    BUT THEY COULD HURT ME.     


446
00:37:14,098 --> 00:37:18,034
                WHAT?           
<i>THEY WOULD COME OUT, THEY</i>       
<i>WOULD SEE THAT YOU WERE SICK,</i>   


447
00:37:18,102 --> 00:37:22,338
    AND THEY WOULD REALIZE THAT 
    I ACCIDENTALLY POISONED YOU.


448
00:37:22,407 --> 00:37:24,540
            AND THAT COULD      
            COST ME MY CAREER.  


449
00:37:24,609 --> 00:37:26,675
        [ Moaning, Gasping ]    
        YOU CAN'T DO THIS.      


450
00:37:26,744 --> 00:37:28,677
            YOU CAN'T DO THIS.  
        [ Recorder Clicking ]   


451
00:37:28,746 --> 00:37:32,115
[ Operator ] TELL ME WHAT       
THE PROBLEM IS, SIR.            
[ Harry ] THEY RAN GEORGE DOWN. 


452
00:37:32,183 --> 00:37:34,884
            YOU GOTTA GET       
            SOMEBODY DOWN HERE. 
            LAWSON AND HILL.    


453
00:37:34,952 --> 00:37:38,587
        RIGHT IN FRONT OF       
        THE CHILDREN'S SHELTER. 
        HURRY. YOU GOTTA HURRY. 


454
00:37:38,656 --> 00:37:41,524
        I'M CALLING IT IN, SIR. 
        IS ANYONE ELSE HURT?    
NO. THEY JUST HIT HIM AND LEFT. 


455
00:37:41,592 --> 00:37:43,860
                [ Clicks Off ]  
YOU'RE A CORONER.               


456
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:49,565
YOUR BUSINESS IS DEAD PEOPLE.   
EVEN WHEN YOU'RE THE ONE        
WHO KILLS THEM. RIGHT, DOCTOR?  


457
00:37:49,634 --> 00:37:53,435
DID YOU HAVE A LITTLE           
TOO MUCH TO DRINK AT            
LAST YEAR'S CHRISTMAS PARTY?    


458
00:37:56,708 --> 00:38:00,576
CAN YOU IMAGINE HOW CHRISTMAS   
GEORGE MUST HAVE FELT WHEN      
YOU HIT HIM WITH YOUR CAR...    


459
00:38:00,644 --> 00:38:03,145
AND LEFT HIM IN THE SNOW?       


460
00:38:03,214 --> 00:38:06,949
<i>HE WENT INTO THE ALLEY</i>          
<i>TO RECOVER, AND YOU HEARD</i>       
<i>OVER YOUR POLICE SCANNER...</i>     


461
00:38:07,018 --> 00:38:09,385
THAT HE WAS STILL ALIVE.        


462
00:38:10,387 --> 00:38:12,921
<i>YOU COULDN'T HAVE THAT,</i>         
<i>COULD YOU?</i>                      


463
00:38:12,990 --> 00:38:15,424
THAT COULD HURT                 
YOUR PRECIOUS CAREER.           


464
00:38:17,562 --> 00:38:22,698
SO YOU WENT BACK TO THE SCENE,  
BEFORE THE POLICE GOT THERE.    


465
00:38:22,767 --> 00:38:27,170
NOW, YOU DIDN'T HAVE            
ANYTHING IN YOUR BAG THAT       
WOULD ACTUALLY KILL HIM,        


466
00:38:27,238 --> 00:38:29,705
BUT YOU DID HAVE SOMETHING      
THAT WOULD PARALYZE HIM.        


467
00:38:29,774 --> 00:38:32,507
HE WAS CONSCIOUS OF EVERYTHING  
THAT WAS HAPPENING TO HIM,      


468
00:38:32,576 --> 00:38:35,010
BUT HE LOOKED DEAD              
TO THE POLICE.                  


469
00:38:35,079 --> 00:38:37,680
    HE WAS JUST A HOMELESS MAN. 


470
00:38:37,749 --> 00:38:40,649
YOU FIGURED, NO ONE             
WOULD MISS HIM, RIGHT?          


471
00:38:40,718 --> 00:38:44,320
    BUT LIKE YOU ALWAYS SAY,    
    BAG 'EM AND TAG 'EM.        


472
00:38:54,799 --> 00:38:59,202
            [ Mumbling ]        
            NO. DON'T DO THAT.  
            I'M NOT REALLY DEAD.


473
00:38:59,270 --> 00:39:03,472
    WELL, IF IT MAKES           
    YOU FEEL ANY BETTER,        
    I'M NOT REALLY A CORONER.   


474
00:39:03,541 --> 00:39:06,308
[ Voice Echoing ]               
BUT EVERYBODY THINKS I AM.      


475
00:39:06,377 --> 00:39:09,144
SO I'M JUST GOING               
TO DECLARE YOU DEAD.            


476
00:39:09,213 --> 00:39:11,947
AND THEY CAN FINISH YOU OFF.    
ON THE SLAB.                    


477
00:39:12,016 --> 00:39:14,483
JUST LIKE                       
YOU FINISHED OFF GEORGE.        


478
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:18,120
            <i> MERRY CHRISTMAS.</i>   


479
00:39:19,257 --> 00:39:21,923
<i>♪♪ [ "Jingle Bells,"</i>            
<i>     Off-tempo ]</i>                


480
00:39:29,467 --> 00:39:32,835
        [ Voice Distant ] WOW.  
        I NEVER GOT TO WORK     
        ON A BOSS BEFORE.       


481
00:39:32,903 --> 00:39:37,139
        WE'LL START CUTTING     
        ON HER AFTER LUNCH.     
        WHO WANTS PUFFER FISH?  


482
00:39:42,446 --> 00:39:45,614
THE EFFECTS OF                  
THE PHENOTRIPTICOL SHOULD       
WEAR OFF IN A FEW HOURS.        


483
00:39:45,683 --> 00:39:49,452
SHE'S GONNA WAKE UP WITH        
A WICKED CASE OF DIARRHEA       
FROM THE FRUITCAKE.             


484
00:39:49,520 --> 00:39:52,688
        MERRY CHRISTMAS, JAROD. 
MERRY CHRISTMAS.                


485
00:39:54,959 --> 00:39:56,892
[ Chuckles ]                    
                <i> [ Knocking ]</i>   


486
00:39:58,195 --> 00:40:00,696
    MERRY CHRISTMAS.            
    HE SAID TO GIVE YOU THIS.   


487
00:40:02,066 --> 00:40:04,667
HE WHO?                         


488
00:40:23,988 --> 00:40:26,989
EXCUSE ME.                      
DR. MARLEY?                     


489
00:40:27,058 --> 00:40:30,459
                        YES?    
I'M TIMOTHY.                    
TIMOTHY RYAN.                   


490
00:40:30,528 --> 00:40:32,461
            GABRIELLE'S BROTHER.


491
00:40:32,530 --> 00:40:37,766
I JUST WANTED TO SAY--          
WELL, THIS DETECTIVE SAID       
YOU IDENTIFIED HER.             


492
00:40:37,835 --> 00:40:42,071
WENT THE EXTRA MILE, HE SAID.   
            I'M SORRY THAT      
            IT TOOK SO LONG.    


493
00:40:42,140 --> 00:40:44,273
            AND I'M SORRY THAT  
            YOU HAD TO FIND OUT 
            AT THIS TIME.       


494
00:40:44,342 --> 00:40:49,945
I'M NOT. IMAGINE WONDERING      
A LIFETIME IF SOMEONE           
YOU LOVE IS OUT THERE OR NOT.   


495
00:40:50,014 --> 00:40:52,581
THANK YOU FOR SAVING            
MY FAMILY THAT HELL.            


496
00:40:53,651 --> 00:40:55,718
THANK YOU.                      


497
00:41:00,992 --> 00:41:04,459
<i>[ Children's Choir ]</i>            
<i>♪ SILENT NIGHT ♪</i>                


498
00:41:04,528 --> 00:41:07,863
<i>♪ HOLY NIGHT ♪</i>                  


499
00:41:07,932 --> 00:41:11,067
<i>♪ ALL IS CALM ♪</i>                 


500
00:41:11,135 --> 00:41:14,136
<i>♪ ALL IS BRIGHT ♪</i>               


501
00:41:14,205 --> 00:41:17,306
<i>♪ ROUND YON VIRGIN ♪</i>            


502
00:41:17,375 --> 00:41:20,476
<i>♪ MOTHER AND CHILD ♪</i>            


503
00:41:20,544 --> 00:41:23,045
<i>♪ HOLY INFANT ♪</i>                 


504
00:41:23,114 --> 00:41:26,849
<i>♪ SO TENDER AND MILD ♪</i>          


505
00:41:26,918 --> 00:41:32,654
<i>♪ SLEEP IN HEAVENLY PEACE ♪</i>     
            <i> [ Phone Ringing ]</i>  


506
00:41:32,723 --> 00:41:36,658
            [ Ringing ]         
    [ Clears Throat ]           


507
00:41:36,727 --> 00:41:39,629
HELLO. DADDY, HELLO.            


508
00:41:39,697 --> 00:41:42,064
I WAS JUST GETTING READY--      


509
00:41:42,133 --> 00:41:45,267
<i>♪♪ [ Piano: "Silent Night" ]</i>    


510
00:41:48,573 --> 00:41:51,807
    I UNDERSTAND. NO.           


511
00:41:51,875 --> 00:41:54,376
WE'LL DO IT NEXT YEAR.          


512
00:41:59,083 --> 00:42:02,150
                    [ Beeps ]   
        [ Exhales ]             


513
00:42:05,389 --> 00:42:07,390
MERRY CHRISTMAS.                


514
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:12,895
<i>♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>                
<i>[ Footsteps ]</i>                   


515
00:42:14,499 --> 00:42:16,866
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>HE'S READY NOW.</i>                 


516
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:25,808
YOU KNOW, I ADMIRE              
YOU, SYDNEY.                    


517
00:42:25,877 --> 00:42:30,413
FOR 30 YEARS, HE JUST           
LIES THERE, AND YET YOU'VE      
NEVER MISSED A CHRISTMAS.       


518
00:42:30,481 --> 00:42:33,482
            IT'S ALL I CAN DO.  
            HE'S THE ONLY FAMILY
            I HAVE.             


519
00:42:33,551 --> 00:42:38,354
    - WHAT ABOUT YOUR SON?      
    - MY SON?                   


520
00:42:38,422 --> 00:42:41,290
        YES. JAROD.             


521
00:42:42,894 --> 00:42:44,827
            JAROD WAS HERE?     


522
00:42:44,895 --> 00:42:47,996
HE STAYED JUST LONG ENOUGH      
TO LEAVE THE GIFT.              


523
00:42:57,508 --> 00:42:59,442
<i>I DON'T KNOW WHAT</i>               
<i>HE SAID TO HIM,</i>                 


524
00:42:59,510 --> 00:43:04,713
BUT WHEN HE PLACED THAT         
IN HIS HAND, I SWEAR I THOUGHT  
I SAW YOUR BROTHER SMILE.       


525
00:43:07,284 --> 00:43:10,185
        [ Chuckles ]            


526
00:43:10,254 --> 00:43:12,855
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>"'TWAS THE NIGHT BEFORE</i>         
<i> CHRISTMAS,</i>                     


527
00:43:12,923 --> 00:43:15,791
<i>"AND ALL THROUGH THE HOUSE,</i>     
<i> NOT A CREATURE WAS STIRRING,</i>   


528
00:43:15,859 --> 00:43:17,927
<i>"NOT EVEN A MOUSE.</i>              
    [ Chuckles ]                


529
00:43:17,995 --> 00:43:20,229
<i>"THE STOCKINGS WERE HUNG</i>        
<i> BY THE CHIMNEY WITH CARE,</i>      


530
00:43:20,298 --> 00:43:22,798
<i>"IN HOPES THAT ST. NICHOLAS</i>     
<i> SOON WOULD BE THERE.</i>           


531
00:43:22,867 --> 00:43:25,868
<i>"THE CHILDREN WERE NESTLED</i>      
<i> ALL SNUG IN THEIR BEDS,</i>        


532
00:43:25,936 --> 00:43:28,404
<i>"WHILE VISIONS OF SUGARPLUMS</i>    
<i> DANCED IN THEIR HEADS.</i>         


533
00:43:28,472 --> 00:43:31,006
<i>"AND MAMA IN HER KERCHIEF,</i>      
<i>  AND I IN MY CAP,</i>              


534
00:43:31,075 --> 00:43:34,009
<i>"HAD JUST SETTLED DOWN</i>          
<i> FOR A LONG WINTER'S NAP.</i>       


535
00:43:34,078 --> 00:43:36,178
<i>"WHEN OUT ON THE LAWN</i>           
<i> THERE AROSE SUCH A CLATTER,</i>    


536
00:43:36,247 --> 00:43:38,881
<i>"I SPRANG FROM MY BED</i>           
<i> TO SEE WHAT WAS THE MATTER.</i>    


537
00:43:38,949 --> 00:43:41,183
<i>"AWAY TO THE WINDOW</i>             
<i> I FLEW LIKE A FLASH,</i>           


538
00:43:41,252 --> 00:43:44,019
<i>"TORE OPEN THE SHUTTERS</i>         
<i> AND THREW UP THE SASH.</i>         


539
00:43:44,088 --> 00:43:46,221
<i>"WHEN WHAT TO MY WONDERING EYE</i>  
<i> SHOULD APPEAR,</i>                 


540
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:49,392
<i>"BUT A MINIATURE SLEIGH</i>         
<i> AND EIGHT TINY REINDEER.</i>       


541
00:43:49,460 --> 00:43:52,762
<i>"WITH A LITTLE OLD DRIVER,</i>      
<i> SO LIVELY AND QUICK,</i>           


542
00:43:52,830 --> 00:43:56,164
<i>"I KNEW IN A MOMENT</i>             
<i> IT MUST BE ST. NICK.</i>           


543
00:43:56,233 --> 00:43:58,867
<i>"AND HE WHISTLED AND SHOUTED</i>    
<i>  AND CALLED THEM BY NAME:</i>      


544
00:43:58,936 --> 00:44:01,804
<i>"'NOW, DASHER! NOW, DANCER!</i>     
<i>   NOW, PRANCER AND VIXEN!</i>      


545
00:44:01,872 --> 00:44:05,207
<i>"ON COMET! ON CUPID!</i>            
<i> ON DONDER AND BLITZEN!'</i>        


546
00:44:05,275 --> 00:44:08,944
    "HE SPRANG TO HIS SLEIGH,   
     TO HIS TEAM GAVE A WHISTLE,


547
00:44:09,012 --> 00:44:11,780
    "AND AWAY THEY ALL FLEW     
     LIKE THE DOWN OF A THISTLE.


548
00:44:11,849 --> 00:44:15,817
    "BUT I HEARD HIM EXCLAIM,   
     ERE HE DROVE OUT OF SIGHT, 


549
00:44:15,886 --> 00:44:21,290
    'HAPPY CHRISTMAS TO ALL,    
     AND TO ALL A GOOD NIGHT.'" 


550
00:44:21,359 --> 00:44:23,825
            [ Giggling ]        


551
00:44:23,894 --> 00:44:26,495
<i>[ Sleigh Bells Jingling ]</i>       
            DID YOU HEAR THAT?  


552
00:44:26,564 --> 00:44:30,365
    -<i> [ Girl, Gasping ] WHAT?</i>   
    - FROM THE OTHER ROOM.      


553
00:44:30,434 --> 00:44:33,635
        - COULD IT BE--         
        - [ Children ] SANTA!   


554
00:44:33,704 --> 00:44:36,038
<i>[ Girl ]</i>                        
<i>LET'S GO IN THE OTHER ROOM!</i>     
<i>UNDER THE TREE!</i>                 


555
00:44:38,275 --> 00:44:41,877
[ Chattering ]                  


556
00:44:45,716 --> 00:44:47,649
A PRESENT FOR ME?               


557
00:44:47,719 --> 00:44:50,452
I WONDER WHO IT'S FROM?         
        LET'S SEE WHAT YOU GOT. 


558
00:44:54,192 --> 00:44:56,192
        WHAT'S IT SAY?          


559
00:44:56,260 --> 00:44:58,861
"FRIENDS MAKE CHRISTMAS SPECIAL.


560
00:44:58,929 --> 00:45:02,797
TO ANGEL, MERRY CHRISTMAS,      
FROM CHRISTMAS GEORGE."         


561
00:46:02,126 --> 00:46:03,125
            [ Mews ]            


